was the greatest educator in the world at that time", "doc_title": "68359_Zutty Singleton oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68359/"}, {"speaker": "Hayes Pillars", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "Booker Pitman was the grandson of the late Booker T. WASHINGTON.", "doc_title": "67426_Hayes Pillars oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/67426/"}, {"speaker": "John W. Bubbles", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "You have to have a certain education to get anywhere. But, however, the Principal said, who's going to take care of Madd Washington? I says, I will take care of him. ... same as what's-his-name, Paul Robeson or Frederick Douglass or Booker T. (Washington).", "doc_title": "60322_John Bubbles oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/60322/"}]}